<section class="module module-part1 ">
     <div class="main-content container">
            <p> At Toshimaen Niwa no Yu, you can enjoy a tranquil bath while overlooking the Japanese Garden. 
                This natural hot spring, abundant with minerals, is drawn from 1445 meters underground. 
                The mineral-rich hot spring water is said to be beneficial for the skin and it also has an effect of boosting 
                blood circulation, so you will stay nice and warm even long after you’ve gotten out of the bath.
            </p>
            <p>
                Aside from the indoor hot spring and the outdoor rock bath, there are also bathtubs for Ne-yu, which is a 
                bath taken while lying down, “micro bubble” bath, which is similar to a Jacuzzi except with much smaller 
                bubbles that are softer on the skin, and carbonated water bath.
                In addition, there is a one-person bathtub made of Shigaraki ware, which is a type of Japanese traditional 
                ceramics that originated in the Shigaraki area of Shiga prefecture.
            </p>
