        <p>The Onsen facility houses a Bade Pool, which originated in Germany as a hydrotherapy
             facility for stretching and massaging underwater and is said to have a number of health 
             benefits. This zone is open to everyone and you need to put on your swimming suits in order to use 
             this facility. The water temperature of the Bade Pool is set at 35 degrees Celsius, which is 
             almost the same temperature as the human body, and thus considered to be relaxing for the body.
        </p>
        <p>
            There are also steam saunas, in which you can sweat out your bodily wastes, hot tubs, outdoor
             natural hot spring Jacuzzi, and Finland-style saunas. Find your favorite type of bath and enjoy! 
